flowchart TB
  subgraph Model
    Base[Base generative model (e.g., UNet / Diffusion model)]
  end

  Base --> Layers[Selected layers (attention, MLP, conv)]
  Layers --> LoRA[LoRA adapters inserted]

  subgraph LoRA_adapter
    A[Rank-r matrix A]
    B[Rank-r matrix B]
    A --> B
    B --> Merge[Add to layer weight during forward]
  end

  LoRA --> Training[Train only A and B (low-rank) + adapter params]
  Training --> Optim[Optimizer & scheduler]
  Training --> Checkpoint[Save LoRA checkpoints (.pt / .safetensors)]

  Checkpoint --> Export[Export adapter bundle (metadata + weights)]
  Export --> Registry[Adapter Registry (/models/adapters)]

  %% Inference merge
  Merge --> Inference[Merge LoRA into base weights at runtime (optional)]
  Inference --> Output[Generated samples / embeddings]

  Note[Key points:\n- LoRA introduces O(d*r) params instead of O(d^2)\n- Fine-tune small adapter parameters only\n- Enables efficient continual/adaptive training]:::note

  classDef note fill:#fff7cc,stroke:#b08900,stroke-width:1px
  class Note note;